  "name": "Cosmic Unfolding",
  "description": "The story of everything — from the Big Bang to you reading this sentence. Thirty milestones in the 13.8-billion-year history of the universe, told with wonder and awe. Each event is a turning point: the moment the first light escaped, the first star ignited, the first planet formed, the first cell divided, the first eye opened. Tiered content for young children (Story) and older readers (Science).\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Camille Flammarion (1842–1925), whose astronomical illustrations in 'Astronomie Populaire' (1880) and 'L'Atmosphère' (1888) combined scientific accuracy with cosmic wonder. Étienne Léopold Trouvelot (1827–1895), whose astronomical pastels at Harvard Observatory captured planets, nebulae, and solar phenomena with remarkable beauty.",
